Module jfx
Package com.CodeSmell.parser

Class RelationshipManager

java.lang.Object
com.CodeSmell.parser.RelationshipManager
public class RelationshipManager extends Object
The RelationshipManager is responsible for adding relations to the CodePropertyGraph object and adding relationships to each CPGClass's outwardRelations attribute.

  • Constructor Summary

    Constructors
    Constructor
    Description
    RelationshipManager(CodePropertyGraph cpg)
    Create a RelationshipManager object which will assign all possible relations, provided a valid CPG and will return a new CPG with relations.

    • assignAssociation

      protected static void assignAssociation(CodePropertyGraph cpg)
      Iterates through the cpg assigning association relationships.

      BIDIRECTIONAL_ASSOCIATION assigned if the source and dest class both store each other as attributes.

      UNIDIRECTIONAL_ASSOCIATION assigned if only one class has the other as a attribute.

      REFLEXIVE_ASSOCIATION assigned if the source and dest class are the same CPGClass object.

    • checkRelationExists

      protected static boolean checkRelationExists(CodePropertyGraph codePropertyGraph, CodePropertyGraph.Relation relationToAdd)
      Determines whether a relation exists within the CodePropertyGraph (matching the exact source, target, type and multiplicity)

      If the relation exists, return true and if it does not exist, return false.

      Parameters:
      relationToAdd - The relation to be added to the provided CodePropertyGraph object.
      Returns:
      boolean - True or False, depending on if the relation exists within cpg

    • returnHighestMultiplicity

      protected static String returnHighestMultiplicity(Map<String,Long> filteredAttributes)
      Return a String representing the highest multiplicity from a map of attribute types.

      This means that if both 1..1 and 1..* are present, the value returned will be 1..*.

      Parameters:
      filteredAttributes - - A map containing attribute type's and a count of how many times this attribute type appeared within a specific CPGClass
      Returns:
      A String representing the highest multiplicity
